This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Domingo R Rodgers not in court, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. appeared by video for Domingo R Rodgers.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in Court Status conference. Discussion placed on the record. Defense advised the court of Global resolution and requested date for Plea hearing. Parties selected date. Court ordered case adjourned, Branch 2.
Plea hearing scheduled for December 1, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Domingo Rashard Rodgers appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz Mr. in court for Domingo Rashard Rodgers.  Prosecuting attorney Thomas Hasle in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court took judicial notice of 15CF1313 and 21CF3695. Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: MPD Officer R. Clementz. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial. Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Case remains calendared for status 10/14/2022 at 8:30am.

Defendant Domingo R Rodgers appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. in court for Domingo R Rodgers.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 

Case in court for a status conference.  Arguments heard as to bail.  Court denies modification of cash bail.  All previously ordered conditions of bail remain in full effect.  Parties anticipate global resolution.  However, no offer has been provided by the State yet.  Matter remains calendared for a preliminary hearing on September 29 at 8:30 AM.  Court further schedules a status conference.  Case adjourned to Branch PE, Rm 146 CJF for preliminary hearing.
Status conference scheduled for October 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5. Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Electronic Monitoring (24 hour curfew). If defendant obtains job to let justice point know. Court orders defendant placed on waiting list if bail posted. Defendant may be released while on waitlist. No driving without a valid license. Court ordered no possession or use dangerous weapons or firearms. No new cases.

Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 2.
Defendant given a copy of complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT DOES QUALIFY FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION. Defense requests waiver of time limits for prelim   Court grants and WAIVES TIME LIMITS for prelim. Case is adjourned for preliminary hearing in Branch PE.

Defendant Domingo R Rodgers in court.  Attorney Frederick F Klimetz mr. in court for Domingo R Rodgers.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. Case in court for return on doctors report.  Parties do not contest the report.   Court finds the defendant is competent to proceed and reinstates the proceedings.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 29, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Status conference scheduled for September 19, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Domingo Rashard Rodgers in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Domingo Rashard Rodgers in custody.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
